Aphalara itadori, the Japanese knotweed psyllid, is a species of psyllid from Japan which feeds on Japanese knotweed (Reynoutria japonica).
It has been licensed by the UK Government for the biological control of Japanese knotweed in England; this was the first time that biological control of a weed was sanctioned in the European Union.The specific name comes from itadori (虎杖, イタドリ), the Japanese name for Japanese knotweed.